6">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/2342767/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Metastases+to+the+breast+from+extramammary+malignancies&amp;author=M+Amichetti&amp;author=B+Perani&amp;author=S+Boi&amp;publication_year=1990&amp;journal=Oncology&amp;pages=257-260&amp;doi=10.1159%2F000226826&amp;pmid=2342767">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">16.</div><div id="r16" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Di Nubila B, Meroni S, Bonello L, Peccatori F, Cassano E, Bellomi M. Breast ductal carcinoma and metastatic lymphoma to the contralateral breast in patient with cutaneous non-Hodgkin lymphoma. <em>Hippokratia</em> 2011;15(1):84–86.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21607043/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Breast+ductal+carcinoma+and+metastatic+lymphoma+to+the+contralateral+breast+in+patient+with+cutaneous+non-Hodgkin+lymphoma&amp;author=B+Di+Nubila&amp;author=S+Meroni&amp;author=L+Bonello&amp;author=F+Peccatori&amp;author=E+Cassano&amp;author=M+Bellomi&amp;publication_year=2011&amp;journal=Hippokratia&amp;pages=84-86&amp;pmid=21607043">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">17.</div><div id="r17" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Zagouri F, Sergentanis TN, Nonni A, et al. Secondary breast lymphoma diagnosed by vacuum-assisted breast biopsy: a case report. <em>J Med Case Reports</em> 2007;1(1):113.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1186/1752-1947-1-113">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.